name: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Appellant, v. Timothy Allan NORTHRUP, Appellee

judges: Before FLAHERTY, C.J., and ZAPPALA, CAPPY, CASTILLE, NIGRO, NEWMAN and SAYLOR, JJ.
parties: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Appellant, v. Timothy Allan NORTHRUP, Appellee.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
Based upon our disposition in Commonwealth v. Williams, 557 Pa. 285, 733 A.2d 593 (1999), we affirm the Order of the Blair County Court of Common Pleas dated January 13, 1998. Furthermore, we remand the matter to the common pleas court for disposition of any remaining issues.
Jurisdiction is relinquished.
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.

attorneys: Jackie Atheron Bernard, Duncansville, for Com.
Loreen M. Kemps, Duncansville, for Timothy Allan Northrup.
